 :tx/rationale "Create task: LIVESTORE-TEST-ALGEBRAIC: Formal verification proptests for LiveStore algebraic properties. CONTEXT: LiveStore write-through has deep algebraic properties that should be tested via property-based testing. The checkpoint-equals-fold invariant (INV-STORE-020) and CRDT commutativity (C4) are the core properties. APPROACH: PROPTEST (in crates/braid/tests/livestore_algebraic.rs): (1) CHECKPOINT_EQUALS_FOLD: For any sequence of 1-20 random transactions, the LiveStore's store.bin (deserialized) produces identical datom set to Store::from_datoms(all txn files). This tests INV-STORE-020. (2) COMMUTATIVITY: For any set of N transactions applied in two different orderings, both produce identical Store states. This tests C4 (CRDT merge by set union). (3) MONOTONIC_GROWTH: For any sequence of writes, live.store().len() is monotonically non-decreasing. This tests C1 (append-only). (4) FITNESS_CONSISTENCY: After any write, live.store().fitness() == Store::from_datoms(all txns).fitness(). This tests MaterializedViews incremental correctness. (5) CRASH_RECOVERY: For any sequence of N writes, if we simulate crash after write k (by deleting store.bin but keeping txn files), LiveStore::open() recovers to the same state as if no crash occurred. (6) COMMAND_SEQUENCE_SAFETY: For any interleaving of observe, task create, task close, harvest operations on a LiveStore, all store invariants hold (positive datom count, valid schema, monotonic frontier). This is the most ambitious test — it validates that arbitrary command sequences can't corrupt the store. ACCEPTANCE: All 6 proptests pass with at least 256 cases each. DEPENDS-ON: LIVESTORE-4. TRACES: INV-STORE-020, C1, C4, ADR-FOUNDATION-034. FILE: crates/braid/tests/livestore_algebraic.rs (new)"
